Windows Attack Surface Analysis with Open-Source Tools
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand attack surface analysis concepts in system security
Enumerate processes and services using command-line tools
Analyze network exposure and identify security risks
Create automated security assessment scripts
Generate comprehensive security reports
Prerequisites
Students should have:

Basic Linux command-line proficiency
Understanding of processes, services, and network concepts
Fundamental Python programming skills
Basic cybersecurity knowledge
Lab Environment
This lab uses pre-configured Linux cloud machines that simulate attack surface analysis concepts. All necessary tools are pre-installed. Click Start Lab to access your environment.

Task 1: System Process and Service Enumeration
Step 1: Install Required Tools
Update your system and install necessary packages:

# Update repositories
sudo apt update

# Install required packages
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip htop net-tools lsof

# Install Python libraries
pip3 install psutil tabulate colorama
