Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Permission denied errors when scanning

Solution: Run scripts with sudo for system-level access
Alternative: Focus on user-accessible resources first
Issue: Python module import errors

Solution: Verify installations with pip3 list
Reinstall: pip3 install --user psutil tabulate colorama
Issue: Empty or incomplete results

Solution: Check if services are running: systemctl status
Verify network connections exist: netstat -an
Issue: Scripts not executing

Solution: Ensure executable permissions: chmod +x script.py
Check Python path: which python3
Conclusion
This lab introduced attack surface analysis concepts using open-source tools and custom Python scripts. You learned to enumerate system processes and services, analyze network exposure, identify vulnerabilities, and generate security assessment reports. These skills are fundamental for security auditing and system hardening.

Key takeaways:

Attack surface analysis identifies potential entry points for attackers
Automated enumeration provides comprehensive system visibility
Risk scoring helps prioritize remediation efforts
Regular security assessments are essential for maintaining security posture
Continue practicing by analyzing different systems and refining your detection capabilities.
